# Hosting environment (SC Prints)

**Railway is no longer used.** Do not suggest Railway deploys, `railway run`, or `RAILWAY_*` env vars.

## Production stack

| Layer | Provider | URL / resource |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Medusa API + Admin | **Fly.io** | `https://sc-prints-backend.fly.dev` (app: `sc-prints-backend`, region: `syd`) |
| Storefront | **Vercel** | `https://sc-prints.com.au` (project may still be named `medusajs-2-0-for-railway-vercel` on Vercel) |
| Postgres | **DigitalOcean** | `DATABASE_URL` on Fly secrets |
| Object storage | **Cloudflare R2** | S3-compatible via `MINIO_*` env (bucket `sc-prints-media`) |
| Redis | **Required in prod** | Set `REDIS_URL` on Fly — without it Medusa uses fake Redis + in-memory sessions |

## Commands agents should use

```bash
# Backend logs / deploy (Fly)
fly logs --app sc-prints-backend
fly deploy --app sc-prints-backend   # from backend/

# One-off scripts on production (Fly SSH — not Railway)
fly ssh console --app sc-prints-backend
cd /app/.medusa/server && npx medusa exec src/scripts/<name>.js

# Local one-off scripts
cd backend && npx medusa exec src/scripts/<name>.ts
```

Always use `/app/.medusa/server` (or `backend/.medusa/server` locally after build) for `medusa exec` on the server image.

## Env vars that must point at the new stack

**Fly secrets (`sc-prints-backend`):** `DATABASE_URL`, `REDIS_URL`, `JWT_SECRET`, `COOKIE_SECRET`, `BACKEND_PUBLIC_URL=https://sc-prints-backend.fly.dev`, `STOREFRONT_URL`, `STORE_CORS`, `ADMIN_CORS`, `AUTH_CORS`, `MINIO_*`, integration keys.

**Vercel production:** `NEXT_PUBLIC_MEDUSA_BACKEND_URL=https://sc-prints-backend.fly.dev`, `NEXT_PUBLIC_BASE_URL=https://sc-prints.com.au`.

**Webhooks:** Stripe/PayPal/ShipStation endpoints use `{BACKEND_PUBLIC_URL}/hooks/...` on Fly, not Railway.

